## 2. Install MCP servers (user scope)

Run each command in PowerShell. Each is one line; copy the whole block.

### 2.1 Perplexity MCP

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --scope user `
  --transport stdio `
  -e PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=REPLACE_PERPLEXITY_KEY `
  perplexity `
  -- npx -y @perplexity-ai/mcp-server
```

### 2.2 Playwright MCP

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --scope user `
  --transport stdio `
  playwright `
  -- npx -y @playwright/mcp@latest
```

> First run will install Playwright's browsers (~200 MB). Allow it to download.

### 2.3 Firecrawl MCP

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --scope user `
  --transport stdio `
  -e FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=REPLACE_FIRECRAWL_KEY `
  firecrawl `
  -- npx -y firecrawl-mcp
```

### 2.4 Glif MCP

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --scope user `
  --transport stdio `
  -e GLIF_API_TOKEN=REPLACE_GLIF_TOKEN `
  glif `
  -- npx -y @glifxyz/glif-mcp-server
```

### 2.5 Chrome DevTools MCP

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --scope user `
  --transport stdio `
  chrome-devtools `
  -- npx -y chrome-devtools-mcp@latest
```

### 2.6 Higgsfield MCP (HTTP transport)

```powershell
claude mcp add `
  --transport http `
  --scope user `
  higgsfield `
  https://mcp.higgsfield.ai/mcp
```

> On first use Claude Code will prompt you to complete an OAuth/login flow in your browser. Follow it once and the session is saved.

